This paper proposes a new neural architecture for graph-to-sequence learning in natural language processing (NLP) applications. The paper focuses on encoding the full structural information contained in the graph, which is a common problem in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also proposes a new model that uses Gated Graph Neural Networks, which is a type of neural network that has been used in many machine learning applications, including computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper addresses the parameter explosion problem, which is a common issue in deep learning, and this could be related to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on two NLP tasks, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), a sub-category that deals with the use of neural networks in various applications.
